Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens, Schäfer - und - Schäferinnen (ehemals Dulwich)" addressed to "Herrn Prof. Dr. Hans-Gerhard Evers Waldstrasse 43 D - 6101 Traisa bei Darmstadt" and dated 15.06.1971

- First subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens") addressed to "Herrn Professor Dr. H. G. Evers Technische Hochschule Darmstadt Institut für Kunstgeschichte" and dated 21.03.1961:
    - Correspondence with the Museum of Koblenz dated 1961
    - Photocopy of a reproduction of 'Sheperds'
- Correspondence with Kurt Meissner dated 1971
- Notes about the painting 'Shepherd and Shepherdess' in Zurich (dated 1971)
- Draft text of the letter for Meissner
- Second subfolder (Annotation: "Justus Müller-Hofstede zwei Hirtenidyllen des späten Rubens Pantheon 24, 1966"):
    - Essay: 'Zwei Hirtenidyllen des späten Rubens', in "Pantheon", n.24, 1966
- Extracts from different publications  
  
Loose documentation reunited with the folder:   
     
- Clear envelope with 3 photos of 'Shepherd and Shepherdes'
- Clear envelope with 2 photos of 'Shepherd and Shepherdes'
